  <p style="font-size:14px;">BPC-157 is a 15-amino-acid peptide derived from human gastric juice that accelerates healing across multiple tissue types: tendons, ligaments, muscle, gut lining, and nerve tissue. It works partly through VEGF-mediated angiogenesis and nitric oxide pathways (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29621842/">Sikiric et al., 2018</a>).</p>
